---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';

const WORKSHOP_TITLE = 'Practical Generative AI Workshops for Teams | Auston Horras';
const WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION =
	'Practical generative AI workshops for teams and leaders. Learn how to work with AI effectively using clear workflows, constraints, and real-world examples.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={WORKSHOP_TITLE} description={WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="page-shell">
			<header class="main-nav">
				<nav class="container nav-inner" aria-label="Primary">
					<a href="/" class="brand">austontatious.dev</a>
					<div class="nav-links">
						<a href="/#hero">Portfolio</a>
						<a href="/#projects">Projects</a>
						<a href="/workshops/" aria-current="page">Workshops</a>
					</div>
					<div class="nav-actions">
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Email</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
							LinkedIn
						</a>
					</div>
				</nav>
			</header>

			<main class="workshop-main">
				<section class="section workshop-hero">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<p class="eyebrow">Executive Workshop Offering</p>
						<h1>You Invested in AI. Is Your Team Seeing the Productivity Gains?</h1>
						<p class="lead workshop-lead">
							Practical generative AI workshops for teams that need real results from tools they already use.
						</p>
						<p class="workshop-intro">
							Most organizations now have access to powerful AI systems. The challenge is turning that access
							into consistent productivity across day-to-day work.
						</p>
						<div class="workshop-hero-actions">
							<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=AI%20Workshop%20Inquiry">
								Inquire About a Workshop
							</a>
							<a class="button button-secondary" href="#format">See Workshop Format</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>The Real Reason AI Productivity Is Inconsistent</h2>
							<p>
								Over the past year, many organizations rolled out generative AI tools across their teams. Budgets
								were approved. Expectations were raised. Employees began experimenting.
							</p>
							<p>
								But results are uneven. Some employees produce strong outcomes with AI while others try it
								briefly and conclude the tools are unreliable.
							</p>
							<p>
								The issue is rarely access to technology. Most organizations already have powerful AI tools
								available. The missing piece is a shared framework for using them effectively in real workflows.
							</p>
							<p>
								Most AI training also has not kept pace with how modern models actually behave. Teams are often
								taught outdated prompt techniques that produce inconsistent results.
							</p>
							<p>
								What organizations actually need is a practical translation layer, turning how AI systems
								behave into repeatable work habits teams can apply in daily work.
							</p>
							<p>
								That translation layer is where most productivity gains are unlocked.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>How This Workshop Solves It</h2>
							<p>
								This workshop closes that gap. Teams learn how modern AI systems behave and how to interact with
								them in ways that produce reliable results.
							</p>
							<p>
								The goal is not to impress participants with demos. The goal is practical methods that improve speed,
								quality, and consistency in the workflows teams already use.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>What Your Team Walks Away With</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>A shared framework for using AI effectively across roles</li>
								<li>More consistent output quality and confidence across the team</li>
								<li>Better judgment about where AI is useful versus risky</li>
								<li>Practical methods for scope, context, and constraint-driven prompting</li>
								<li>Workflows teams can apply immediately to writing, analysis, planning, and operations</li>
							</ul>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Why This Perspective Is Different</h2>
							<p>
								Many workshops are delivered as trend commentary. This workshop is taught from the perspective of
								someone who builds AI systems and agent workflows in implementation reality.
							</p>
							<p>
								The focus is translating model behavior into practical business use. RN experience is also useful for
								healthcare and other regulated environments where reliability matters.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel" id="format">
							<h2>Workshop Format</h2>
							<p>
								The workshop can be delivered as a 60-minute executive briefing or as a 2-4 hour team
								workshop. Sessions can be customized for technical teams, operational groups, or
								cross-functional organizations and are available either remotely or on-site.
							</p>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Example Live Demonstrations</h2>
							<p>
								During the workshop, participants see real examples of how modern AI systems behave in
								practical work settings, including turning inconsistent AI usage into repeatable workflows,
								converting rough ideas into structured plans or technical specifications, and using AI to
								critique and strengthen business documents.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Who This Workshop Is For</h2>
							<p>
								This workshop is designed for organizations that have already invested in AI tools but are
								still figuring out how to use them effectively across teams.
							</p>
							<p>
								It tends to be most valuable for leadership teams trying to translate AI investment into
								measurable productivity, for organizations where some employees are succeeding with AI while
								others struggle to get consistent results, for technical or operational teams responsible for
								integrating AI into real workflows, and for regulated or high-reliability environments where
								output quality matters.
							</p>
							<p>
								If your organization already has access to modern AI systems but has not yet developed
								consistent ways to apply them in daily work, this workshop focuses on exactly that problem.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<div class="workshop-cta">
							<h2>Bring This Workshop to Your Team</h2>
							<p>
								If your organization has already invested in AI tools but is not yet seeing the productivity gains
								it expected, I can help your teams use these systems effectively in real workflows.
							</p>
							<div class="cta-actions">
								<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=AI%20Workshop%20Inquiry">
									Contact by Email
								</a>
								<a
									class="button button-secondary"
									href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noreferrer"
								>
									LinkedIn
								</a>
							</div>
							<a class="back-link workshop-back-link" href="/#hero">Back to portfolio</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
			</main>

			<footer class="site-footer">
				<div class="container footer-inner">
					<p>Calm systems for clear outcomes.</p>
					<div class="footer-links">
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Contact</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
							LinkedIn
						</a>
						<a href="https://github.com/austontatious" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
